# Optional Chaining Nullish Only

- Use `?.` only when the root expression is truly nullable/optional by type.
- Do not use `?.` on values that should exist; prefer direct access or explicit guards.
- When a value should exist by invariant, prefer `(expr ?? never())` over optional chaining.
- Keep nullability handling explicit and local so unsafe paths are obvious.

## Example

```ts
// ❌ Avoid (hides a required invariant)
const refs = callee.arguments[argumentIndex]?.refs

// ✅ Prefer
const refs = (callee.arguments[argumentIndex] ?? never()).refs
```
